features: Complete Cutlery Set: This set includes 30 knives, 30 forks, and 30 spoons, providing you with a comprehensive disposable cutlery solution. Whether it's a family gathering, a picnic, or a large event, this set ensures you have enough utensils for everyone.

Food-Grade Heat-Resistant Material: Our disposable plastic cutlery set is made from food-grade and heat-resistant material, ensuring safety and durability. The high-quality plastic construction guarantees reliable performance without any risk of melting or releasing harmful substances.

Sturdy and Durable: Each piece in the set is designed to be sturdy and durable, allowing you to easily handle various types of food. From slicing through meats with the knife to enjoying salads with the fork and indulging in desserts with the spoon, this cutlery set meets all your dining needs.

Transparent Design: The transparent design adds a modern and elegant touch to your table setting. It not only allows for easy visibility while using but also complements any tableware or decor, making your dining experience more enjoyable.

Easy-to-Open Slide-Out Packaging: Our disposable cutlery set features a convenient slide-out packaging. Just pull the tab, and the cutlery set effortlessly slides out, ready for immediate use. No more struggling with stubborn packaging or searching for tools to open it. With our user-friendly design, take out your utensils has never been easier. Perfect for parties, picnics, or on-the-go meals, our easy-to-open slide-out packaging adds convenience to your dining experience.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great quality disposable cutlery - actually cuts meat!
reviews.reviewText: Made of thick hard plastic, these plastic ware pieces are pretty sturdy. They don’t bend when you try to stab something with a fork or cut something with a knife - they actually do the job they were made for. The cutting surface of the knife is actually sharp and rough, and does cut meat. They are a good size for your hand (not too small). They aren’t indestructible, and can snap if pressed too hard (but it would have to be pretty hard). I really like the packaging - they come in a box with a slide-out tray that separates each type of cutlery in a separate bin. Good quality, reasonably priced.
